sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The cI regulated promoter is based on the pR promtoer from bacteriohage lambda. The promoter has two two DNA binding sites for lambda cI repressor BBa_C0051. cI binding results in repression of transcription. The specific sequence used here is based on the cI repressible promoter used in the Elowitz repressilator (and references therein).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
In order to address concerns about the promoter transcribing in the reverse direction, we have removed the -35 and -10 signals responsible for the promoter activity in the reverse direction. (More details needed here! DE, 2/24/03)

Incompatible with host expressing cI repressor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: AckA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This coding is the acetate kinase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: We got this part from the mutant of E.coli strain K12, DH5α,using PCR with the primers we design by ourselves.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We got this part from the mutant of E.coli strain K12, DH5α,using PCR with the primers we design by ourselves. This coding is the acetate kinase. Acetate kinase was employed as an ATP regeneration system for polyphosphate synthesis. Acording to the paper Genetic Improvement of Escherichia coli for Enhanced Biological Removal of Phosphate from Wastewater, increasing the dosage of the E. coli genes encoding polyphosphate kinase (ppk), acetate kinase (ackA), and the phosphate-inducible transport system (pstS, pstC, pstA, and pstB)could enhance E.coli???s ability of biological removal of phosphate. And the highest rates of Pi removal were obtained by strain MV1184 containing pEP03 (ppk and ackA).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Acording to the paper Genetic Improvement of Escherichia coli for Enhanced Biological Removal of Phosphate from Wastewater, increasing the dosage of the E. coli genes encoding polyphosphate kinase (ppk), acetate kinase (ackA), and the phosphate-inducible transport system (pstS, pstC, pstA, and pstB)could enhance E.coli???s ability of biological removal of phosphate. And the highest rates of Pi removal were obtained by strain MV1184 containing pEP03 (ppk and ackA).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Chang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1217002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is from Kingella oralis (ATCC 51147) genomic DNA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding sequence of polyphosphate kinase (ppk1)(E.C. 2.7.4.1) from Kingella oralis (ATCC 51147), ppk1 catalyzes the formation of polyphosphate from ATP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We choose to amplify ppk1 gene from Tannerella forsythia (ATCC 43037) since the sequence does not contain any of the illegal restriction sites.
